íŸ@4cf1f643625a11eb84e1d30b8badfaea1c1f79c52f28e3e52c0deb781279086d⁄êTitle: title: bits xor
Path: Examples
Content:
Apply bits xor to two numbers
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> 2 | bits xor 2
0

```
Apply bitwise xor to a list of numbers
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> [8 3 2] | bits xor 2
‚ï≠‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚î¨‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚ïÆ
‚îÇ 0 ‚îÇ 10 ‚îÇ
‚îÇ 1 ‚îÇ  1 ‚îÇ
‚îÇ 2 ‚îÇ  0 ‚îÇ
‚ï∞‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚î¥‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚ïØ


```
Apply bitwise xor to binary data
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> 0x[ca fe] | bits xor 0x[ba be]
Length: 2 (0x2) bytes | null_char printable whitespace ascii_other non_ascii
00000000:   70 40                                                p@


```
Apply bitwise xor to binary data of varying lengths with specified endianness
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> 0x[ca fe] | bits xor 0x[aa] --endian big
Length: 2 (0x2) bytes | null_char printable whitespace ascii_other non_ascii
00000000:   ca 54                                                √óT


```
Apply bitwise xor to input binary data smaller than the operand
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> 0x[ff] | bits xor 0x[12 34 56] --endian little
Length: 3 (0x3) bytes | null_char printable whitespace ascii_other non_ascii
00000000:   ed 34 56                                             √ó4V


```
